###secure login 
ssh -i MyDemoKeyPair.pem ec2-user@Public-IP-Address

ssh -i MyDemoKeyPair.pem ec2-user@Private-IP-Address

###secure copy
scp -i MyDemoKeyPair.pem MyDemoKeyPair.pem ec2-user@<Public-EC2-IP>:/home/ec2-user/

###chmod
chmod 400 MyDemoKeyPair.pem

###curl 
curl http://private-website-bucket.s3-website-<region>.amazonaws.com
curl <Private-EC2-IP>

###aws
aws configure
$ aws configure
AWS Access Key ID [None]: AKIAIOSFODNN7EXAMPLE
AWS Secret Access Key [None]: wJalrXUtnFEMI/K7MDENG/bPxRfiCYEXAMPLEKEY
Default region name [None]: us-west-1
Default output format [None]: json

###list s3 buckets
aws s3 ls
aws s3 ls --region eu-west-1

###Start an EC2 instance:
aws ec2 start-instances --instance-ids <instance-id>
aws ec2 start-instances --instance-ids i-1234567890abcdef --region us-west-2

###Stop an EC2 instance:
aws ec2 stop-instances --instance-ids <instance-id>
aws ec2 stop-instances --instance-ids i-1234567890abcdef --region eu-central-1

###Reboot an EC2 instance:
aws ec2 reboot-instances --instance-ids <instance-id>
aws ec2 reboot-instances --instance-ids i-1234567890abcdef --region us-west-2

###Terminate an EC2 instance:
aws ec2 terminate-instances --instance-ids <instance-id>

###Get the status of an EC2 instance:
aws ec2 describe-instance-status --instance-ids <instance-id>
aws ec2 describe-instances --filters "Name=instance-state-name,Values=running" --region us-west-2

###List all running EC2 instances in the ap-southeast-1 region
aws ec2 describe-instances --filters Name=instance-state-name,Values=running --region ap-southeast-1

###Replace <instance-id> with the actual ID of the instance you want to check the status of.
